🗣️ **PAI**: US-013 complete. Created salesblocks and activities schema with proper RLS policies. Salesblocks track timed focus sessions with scheduling, status, and calendar integration fields. Activities log all contact interactions (calls, emails, social, meetings, notes) with outcomes and duration tracking. Managers can view team data and assign salesblocks. All indexes in place for fast querying. Ready for US-014 (Create a salesblock form).

★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────
- **Manager delegation pattern**: The `assigned_by` field enables managers to create salesblocks for team members, with RLS policies checking both user_id (for self-created) and manager role + team_id match (for assigned work)
- **Activity linkage**: salesblock_id is optional on activities (SET NULL), allowing activities to be logged independently OR during a salesblock session - this flexibility supports both structured (salesblock) and ad-hoc outreach workflows
- **Dual duration tracking**: duration_minutes on salesblocks = planned session length; duration_seconds on activities = actual call/meeting length - this distinction enables session adherence reporting vs individual activity metrics
